    <StatementCodes>
      <StatementCode>CCSS.Math.Content.6.EE.B.8</StatementCode>
    </StatementCodes>
    <Statements>
      <Statement>Write an inequality of the form &lt;i&gt;x&lt;/i&gt; &amp;gt; &lt;i&gt;c&lt;/i&gt; or &lt;i&gt;x&lt;/i&gt; &amp;lt; &lt;i&gt;c&lt;/i&gt; to represent a constraint or condition in a real-world or mathematical problem. Recognize that inequalities of the form &lt;i&gt;x&lt;/i&gt; &amp;gt; &lt;i&gt;c&lt;/i&gt; or&lt;i&gt; x&lt;/i&gt; &amp;lt; c have infinitely many solutions; represent solutions of such inequalities on number line diagrams.</Statement>
